limerick_list.text:
My accommodativeness fills me with pride;
With indulgence I'm oversupplied.
They say, "Wow, that guy's pliable!
In that, Mike's reliable;
His adaptiveness can't be denied."

She was marrying some little twit;
Cousin Sid didn't like it one bit!
Sally's letter, invitatory,
Was stirring (excitatory);
It sent him right into a fit.

Every animal found in the zoo
Ambled onto the ark two-by-two:
Two impalas, who leapt;
Two iguanas, who crept;
Two guanacos, two gnats, and two gnu.

Past time: black-bellied gallinule tag;
Now it's grey-breasted crake for my flag.
I have just changed my name,
Underneath I'm the same;
'Cross the marshland I still zig and zag.

An old Roman bought Parmesan cheese,
Prosciutto, ricotta, and peas;
Some garlic, salami,
A pound of pastrami;
And how did he pay?  Why, with aes!

Anecdotalists deal in the riches
Of language.  They're glib sons-a-bitches.
They speak anecdotally;
We laugh at them totally;
Their anecdotes leave us in stitches!

A location that's forward in space;
Where your forehead is found on your face;
Here warm air meets with cold;
There men fight, we are told:
Note that front is the term to embrace.

She's wearing best satin and lace;
Applied scent in a secretive place;
Now she puts on foundation,
(She'll be a sensation!)
Mascara and lipstick — her face.

You're the person on whom I depend;
You're the one I would back to the end;
You're the port in my storm;
You're encouraging, warm
And unparallelled: you're my best friend.

Your outbursts are getting prolific;
Our prayer group's no longer pacific.
We get no relief
From your pain and your grief;
And it's spreading — we're all dolorific.

Sad to note, my dead goat's in a boat.
Got George angry; it shat in his moat.
On my goat I'd been doting;
Found 'er shot, bod a-floating;
George, hot, his goat got, got my goat.

The OEDILF is a labor of love;
Rhyme and meter, all combos thereof.
Words swim in our crania,
Causing this mania;
Skulldrudgery?  Nope — see above.

There are three ways to use anti-icing:
There's no glaze on the cake Jan is slicing;
Dean Bob often prays,
"Please, no ice on school days";
Ice finds sprayed airplane wings unenticing.

My heart aches since you walked out the door;
I feel bad (country singers, keep score!).
Then with frostbite, my thumb
And eight fingers went numb;
I feel badly (tactility's poor).

A gal with two lovers was sated
By a life which was rather X-rated.
Mon, Wed, Fri — she had John;
Tue, Thur, Sat — it was Ron;
And on Sun? Well she just alternated.

To instill fear/uncertainty/doubt
(FUD), spread some rumors about:
They had deadlines and missed 'em;
There are bugs in their system;
And your app is soon coming out.

Many zoos that are small are giraffeless;
When comedians bomb, they are laughless;
And when something's pure gold,
Without fault, I am told,
One can say that the paragon's chaffless.

I'm complainant and he's the defendant;
Yes, Your Honor, my son and descendant.
He lives home, pays no rent,
Which I really resent;
He's too old to remain a dependent!

To the music's conclusion we wend;
Every rhythm and chord sets a trend.
We go slow, reverential,
For phrases cadential;
The song is now over.  The End.

The Abbot was crabby and cross;
He would soon show these monks who was boss.
"This manuscript's hazy—
Quite crabby—you're lazy;
And blots mean half rations: your loss."

A promise 'tween lovers, soft spoken;
A little glass trinket, a token;
Her spirit; her heart;
My left leg, for a start;
All are things I've regrettably broken.

For my furlough, no way I'll go home;
Leaves of absence I won't spend in Nome!
I'll go topless in Nice,
And in Mykonos, Greece;
Then I'll top off my tops off in Rome.

Ex-car nation: we've run out of fuel;
No services; transport by mule;
Corpses rot. As we stare,
Vultures pick their bones bare.
Excarnation — the act of a ghoul.

Herein there are seventeen E's;
Nineteen S's, two X's and D's;
Five H's, three V's,
A's, F's, W's; two G's,
U's; four O's; six R's, I's; eight N's, T's.

Alder-liefest, there's no one above thee;
Forsooth, I adore thee and love thee;
But the eve is soon gone—
The bar closeth anon!
Prithee, out of my way, lest I shove thee.

I love dwarsliggers: very small books
One can carry in all kinds of nooks;
Made of paper as thin
As an onion's slim skin;
Cell-phone sized, well-designed, with good looks.
